==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|sleen|lang=enm}}, {{term|slayn|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term/t|ang|slēan||to strike, beat, smite, stamp, forge, sting, slay, kill, impact}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*slahaną||to fight, strike, kill}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*slak-||to hit, strike, throw}}. Cognate with {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|slaan||to beat, hit, strike|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|nds|-}} {{term|slaan||hit, strike|lang=nds}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|schlagen||to beat, hit, strike (ein Schlag: a hit, a strike) |lang=de}}, {{etyl|da|-}} and {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|slå||to knock, beat, strike|lang=sv}}, {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|slá||to strike|lang=is}}. Related to {{l|en|slaughter}}, {{l|en|onslaught}}.

